# Repo Test Policy

This skill defines the repository's required automated coverage rules.

Use it before deciding whether tests are optional.

## Required Coverage By Change Type

- Routing changes, intercepted routes, modal routing, browser history, URL/query-param UI state, and multi-step browser flows:
  Playwright is required when the repository already supports Playwright, unless impossible.
- Modal, dialog, overlay, or back/forward navigation behavior:
  Playwright is required when the repository already supports Playwright, unless impossible.
- Pure transforms, parsers, normalizers, selectors, and data-only services:
  Vitest-style coverage is required unless impossible.
- Provider, store, reducer, state, or hook logic that drives UI behavior:
  Vitest-style or focused integration coverage is required unless impossible.
- Accessibility-critical interactive surfaces:
  Update automated assertions in the most suitable existing layer when practical.

## Waiver Rules

- "Manual QA only" is not sufficient when the repository already has a suitable automated test layer.
- If no new or updated automated test is added, the rationale must name:
  - why the required layer could not be used, or
  - why existing automated coverage is already sufficient
- Every waiver must also name what still remains unverified.

## Planner Requirements

- Record the required test layer in `PLAN.md`.
- Name the likely affected test files in `FILE_SPECS.md` when possible.
- Surface any likely coverage gap early instead of leaving it to the tester.

## Tester Requirements

- Add or update the required automated tests by change type.
- Keep new coverage focused on the changed behavior.
- Treat the required layer as part of the feature deliverable, not optional follow-up work.

## Verifier Requirements

- Confirm that required automated coverage was added or explicitly waived.
- Treat missing required automated coverage as blocking unless the waiver is concrete and justified.
